msgid "Emacs records a list of changes made in the buffer text, so you can undo recent changes.  This is done using the @code{undo} command, which is bound to @kbd{C-/} (as well as @kbd{C-x u} and @kbd{C-_}).  Normally, this command undoes the last change, moving point back to where it was before the change.  The undo command applies only to changes in the buffer; you can't use it to undo cursor motion."
